Diamond Platnumz has announced his EP is coming out on Friday. The EP comes before the official release of his album. The Tanzanian singer announced this on Instagram, saying his album will be a 12-track project. "51 songs on my album folder, while all I needed was just 12 songs for the album," he wrote. Adding, "I think I'll release an EP before my 12 lucky songs album." Diamond released his last album in 2018, titled, 'A Boy From Tandale'. About his EP, Diamond wrote that it drops this week on Friday. "#FOA it's the EP Hashtag. Guess the Longform?" He has not given more details on the names of the two projects.